cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper introduces a dataset of CAD models for research on geometric deep learning methods and applications. The dataset includes ground truth for differential quantities, patch segmentation, geometric feature detection, and shape reconstruction. The paper also performs a large-scale benchmark for estimation of surface normals, comparing existing data-driven methods and evaluating their performance against both the ground truth and traditional normal estimation methods. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.GR (Graphics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
